The paper discusses the intersection of machine learning and data management, specifically focusing on the challenges of sourcing data and features for ML tasks over relational databases. This suggests that cs.DB (Databases) is a likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates the effects of avoiding key-foreign key joins on three popular complex classifiers, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the behavior of these classifiers and identifies open questions, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper conducts an extensive experimental study, which could also fall under the scope of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
